codex
The sequential 100→50+50 case is fixed, but the “never exceeds parent net” claim is not fully enforced: allocation is read-then-insert and the existing advisory lock is scoped by `(wo_id, output_type)`, so concurrent registrations of different output types can both allocate from the same remaining parent quantity. I also found that mixed consumption UoMs are summed and labeled with `min(uom)`, which is dimensionally unsafe; the test reimplements the SQL with JavaScript `Number` and does not execute or prepare the real query.
